{"parse":{"title":"Broken Chair","pageid":18161883,"revid":829478002,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:BrokenChair.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/BrokenChair.jpg/250px-BrokenChair.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"333\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/BrokenChair.jpg/375px-BrokenChair.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/BrokenChair.jpg/500px-BrokenChair.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1200\" data-file-height=\"1600\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:BrokenChair.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Broken Chair on the Place des Nations, Geneva</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Broken_Chair_United_Nations_Geneva.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Broken_Chair_United_Nations_Geneva.jpg/220px-Broken_Chair_United_Nations_Geneva.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Broken_Chair_United_Nations_Geneva.jpg/330px-Broken_Chair_United_Nations_Geneva.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Broken_Chair_United_Nations_Geneva.jpg/440px-Broken_Chair_United_Nations_Geneva.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3264\" data-file-height=\"2448\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Broken_Chair_United_Nations_Geneva.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Broken Chair in Geneva</div></div></div>\n<p><i><b>Broken Chair</b></i> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Monumental_sculpture\" title=\"Monumental sculpture\">monumental sculpture</a> in wood by the Swiss artist <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Daniel_Berset&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Daniel Berset (page does not exist)\">Daniel Berset</a>, constructed by the carpenter <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Louis_Gen%C3%A8ve&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Louis Gen\u00e8ve (page does not exist)\">Louis Gen\u00e8ve</a>. It is constructed of 5.5 tons of <a href=\"/wiki/Wood\" title=\"Wood\">wood</a> and is 12 metres (39 feet) high. \n</p><p>It depicts a giant <a href=\"/wiki/Chair\" title=\"Chair\">chair</a> with a broken leg and stands across the street from the <a href=\"/wiki/Palace_of_Nations\" title=\"Palace of Nations\">Palace of Nations</a>, in <a href=\"/wiki/Geneva\" title=\"Geneva\">Geneva</a>. It symbolises opposition to <a href=\"/wiki/Land_mine\" title=\"Land mine\">land mines</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Cluster_bomb\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Cluster bomb\">cluster bombs</a>, and acts as a reminder to politicians and others visiting Geneva.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notes_and_references\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes and references</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Broken_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><i>Broken Chair</i> is an original project of <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Paul_Vermeulen&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Paul Vermeulen (page does not exist)\">Paul Vermeulen</a>, co-founder and director of <a href=\"/wiki/Handicap_International\" title=\"Handicap International\">Handicap International</a> Suisse. In October 1996 he commissionned to the artist a monumental chair of over 10 meters high, with a torn leg, to be installed on the place des Nations. The objective was to get the largest possible number of States to sign the Ottawa Treaty on landmines in December 1997. The sculpture was erected by Handicap International in front of the main entrance to the <a href=\"/wiki/Palais_des_Nations\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Palais des Nations\">Palais des Nations</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Geneva\" title=\"Geneva\">Geneva</a> on the 18th of August 1997, where it was intended to remain for three months, until the signing of the <a href=\"/wiki/Ottawa_Treaty\" title=\"Ottawa Treaty\">Ottawa Treaty</a> in December 1997 in Ottawa. Following ratification by 40 countries, the Treaty became effective as an instrument of international law on 1 March 1999.\n</p><p>The failure of significant countries to sign the Treaty and the strong public support for the sculpture caused it to be left in place until 2005, when it was removed to allow extensive remodelling of the Palais des Nations.  After completion of the work, it was reinstalled in the same place in front of the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Nations_Office_at_Geneva\" title=\"United Nations Office at Geneva\">United Nations Office at Geneva</a> on 26 February 2007.\n</p><p>The reinstallation of <i>Broken Chair</i> in February 2007 was officially dedicated by Handicap International to support the signature of an international treaty on a ban on Cluster Bombs (<a href=\"/wiki/Convention_on_Cluster_Munitions\" title=\"Convention on Cluster Munitions\">Convention on Cluster Munitions</a>), which was signed in Oslo in December 2008.\n</p><p>The work was the property of the sculptor until 2004, when he transferred ownership to Handicap International.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Broken_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Other giant chair sculptures are <i><a href=\"/wiki/Chair_(sculpture)\" title=\"Chair (sculpture)\">Chair</a></i> in the US, and the temporary <i>The Writer</i> on <a href=\"/wiki/Hampstead_Heath\" title=\"Hampstead Heath\">Hampstead Heath</a> in London.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes_and_references\">Notes and references</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Broken_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes and references\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n</div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Broken_Chair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><span class=\"official-website\"><span class=\"url\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://broken-chair.com/\">Official website</a></span></span></li></ul>\n<p><br />\nThe article was translates from the <a href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Broken_Chair\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"fr:Broken Chair\">French Wikipedia entry</a> (as of June 2008), with some additional input from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.thewip.net/contributors/2007/05/a_chair_can_be_a_powerful_symb.html\">[1]</a>.\n</p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span id=\"coordinates\"><a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">Coordinates</a>: <span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Broken_Chair&amp;params=46.2226_N_6.139_E_source:GoogleMaps_type:landmark_region:CH-GE\"><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">46\u00b013\u203221\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">6\u00b008\u203220\u2033E</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">46.2226\u00b0N 6.139\u00b0E</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">46.2226; 6.139</span></span></span></a></span></span></span>\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:David_face.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/David_face.png/40px-David_face.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"36\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/David_face.png/60px-David_face.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/David_face.png/80px-David_face.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"140\" data-file-height=\"127\" /></a></td><td><i>This sculpture article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?ti